cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS

The paper discusses an optimization method for deep neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, it focuses on the efficiency and effectiveness of line search approaches for DNNs. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance on several datasets and architectures, which suggests that it could also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of conjugate gradient and hyperparameter grid searches suggests it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the convexity of the loss function, which could also place it under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
